(0, 'SQUIB. A small satirical or political temporary jeu d''esprit,\r\n  which, like the firework of that denomination, sparkles,\r\n  bounces, stinks, and vanishes.'),
(0, 'It''s said that pigeons are the smartest people around; they''re always getting\r\nthe drop on the rest of us.\r\n\r\n	-- Anonymous'),
(0, 'Clans of long ago that wanted to get rid of their unwanted people without killing them \r\nuse to burn their houses down - hence the expression "to get fired."'),
(0, 'New York-- to that tall skyline I come\nFlyin'' in from London to your door\nNew York-- lookin'' down on Central Park\nWhere they say you should not wander after dark.\nNew York.\n		-- Simon and Garfunkle'),
(0, 'When smashing monuments, save the pedstals -- they always come in handy.\r\n		-- Stanislaw J. Lem, "Unkempt Thoughts"'),
