(0, 'Proverbs 7:1-5\n1. My son, keep my words and store up my commands within you.\n2. Keep my commands and you will live; guard my teachings as the \napple of your eye.\n3. Bind them on your fingers; write them on the tablet of your heart.\n4. Say to wisdom, "You are my sister," and call understanding your \nkinsman;\n5. they will keep you from the adulteress, from the wayward wife with \nher seductive words.'),
